The topics are presented in a chronological order: transition from Stone Age to early metal periods, Copper-, Bronze- and Iron Ages, metalwork in the Antiquity and Middle Ages, transition to water powered workshops, Early Modern metalwork, and 19th-20th century rural smithies in Estonia.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of developments in metallurgy and their relation to Estonian metal working.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student will understand the prerequisites, reasons and consequences of the introduction of metals.
